# Frontend domain

You own the slick user experience: layout, motion, pages, client state, forms.

## Do

- Brand-first, atmospheric UI (see user frontend design rules).
- Render persisted + simulated state; send user intents through APIs/contracts.
- Keep first viewport focused; avoid dashboard clutter on marketing/landing surfaces.

## Do not

- Change DB schema or migrations.
- Implement box-score math or GM decision trees.
- Duplicate business rules that belong in `sim/` or `gm/`.

## Hand-offs

- Need new data shapes → propose in `shared/`, Persistence implements.
- Need new actions (trade, sim game) → call existing contracts; don't invent local fake rules.
